data.description: LOOKING FOR A HOME IN A QUIET AREA?  This 4-bedroom, 3-1/2 bath home sitting on 1.06 acres of land in a cul-de-sac street may be just what you are wanting for you and your family. This home features a large living room for entertaining, separate den with wood burning fireplace, spiral staircase leading to upstairs bedroom, kitchen with Corian counters and movable island, formal dining room, and much more.  Enjoy your afternoons under the covered patio overlooking the beautiful view of the property.  If you enjoy fresh vegetables, there is also a beautiful garden growing in the back yard.  There have been a lot of updates/replacements in the past few years which include a new roof, gutters and gutter guards which are a year old, septic system, partial fence, 1 a/c unit, toilets, receptacles and ceiling fans and new shutters. They have also installed a 30-amp plug in for an RV and 50-am plug for a generator.  Sellers are so motivated that they are leaving the dual generator, refrigerator, patio furniture and metal shelf in the garage and offering $2,500 towards buyers closing costs. Home being sold AS IS.
